'''''Babruvahana''''' is a 1977 Indian [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada]] mythological film directed by [[Hunsur Krishnamurthy]] starring [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] in a dual role. The supporting cast features [[B. Saroja Devi]], [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]], [[Jaimala (actress)|Jayamala]], [[Vajramuni]], [[Thoogudeepa Srinivas]] and [[Ramakrishna (Kannada actor)|Ramakrishna]]. The movie is based on one of the [[Mahabharata]] character [[Babruvahana]].

The film won two awards at the 1976–77 [[Karnataka State Film Awards]] — [[Karnataka State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] (Rajkumar) and [[Karnataka State Film Award for Best Sound Recording|Best Sound Recording]] (S. P. Ramanathan). The movie saw a theatrical run of 25 weeks.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20070717135525/http://www.chitratara.com/showCelbProfile.asp?newsid=8</ref>

The movie was dubbed in Telugu. It was also dubbed in Hindi as  '''''Veer Arjun''''' in 1977.<ref>https://www.cinestaan.com/movies/veer-arjun-4725</ref>

